subsection.def:
legislation
                    (法例) means legislation that can be amended by
                an Ordinance;

subparagraph.content:
any work or service normally required of a person who is under
                        detention in consequence of a lawful order of a court, or of a person during
                        conditional release from such detention;

any service of a military character and, where conscientious objection
                        is recognized, any national service required by law of conscientious
                        objectors;

paragraph.content:
to examine, or have examined, the witnesses against him and to obtain the
                    attendance and examination of witnesses on his behalf under the same conditions
                    as witnesses against him;

to vote and to be elected at genuine periodic elections which shall be by
                universal and equal suffrage and shall be held by secret ballot, guaranteeing the
                free expression of the will of the electors;

to provide that, for a period of 1 year beginning on the first anniversary
                    of the commencement date, this Ordinance is subject to such of the Ordinances
                    listed in the Schedule as are specified in the amendment;

paragraph.continued:
before the second anniversary of the commencement date, under or by any
                    Ordinance listed in the Schedule that is specified in the amendment;
                    and
